If you help me, I swear an oath

14:24.104 --> 14:26.039
we'll find the guy that framed you.

14:26.123 --> 14:28.208
All right, I will show
you what I was doing

14:28.292 --> 14:29.784
when the heist went down.

14:29.868 --> 14:31.068
(groans): Oh.

14:31.152 --> 14:34.047
It's so embarrassing, it has to be true.

14:34.131 --> 14:35.630
Give me your phone.

14:39.378 --> 14:42.130
This is what I do every
day at that time,

14:42.214 --> 14:43.965
the time of the crime.

14:44.049 --> 14:47.918
As you will see, I walk
into my private space,

14:48.002 --> 14:50.087
I gargle,

14:50.171 --> 14:54.107
and then, God help me, I...

14:55.060 --> 14:56.903
- ♪<i> Good times and bum times</i> ♪
- ("I'm Still Here" playing)

14:56.987 --> 14:59.930
♪ <i>I've seen them all and, my dear</i> ♪

15:00.014 --> 15:02.820
♪ <i>I'm still here</i> ♪

15:02.904 --> 15:04.968
♪ <i>Plush velvet sometimes</i> ♪

15:05.052 --> 15:07.104
♪ <i>Sometimes just pretzels and beer</i> ♪

15:07.188 --> 15:08.272
(grunts)

15:08.356 --> 15:09.831
♪ <i>But I'm here...</i> ♪

15:12.861 --> 15:16.831
Now you know. When I'm
alone, I sing show tunes.

15:16.915 --> 15:20.031
You didn't steal those
wallets. You stole my heart.

15:20.115 --> 15:21.777
Leave it on.

15:21.861 --> 15:25.432
♪ <i>Ten years a mob boss,
hits and whacks</i> ♪

15:25.516 --> 15:29.710
♪ <i>Bought judges and mayors,
and never paid tax...</i> ♪

15:29.794 --> 15:31.293
- Okay, that's enough.
- (music stops)

15:32.289 --> 15:33.946
Definitely enough.

15:37.361 --> 15:39.553
We're gonna get you out, today.

15:39.637 --> 15:40.646
(groans)

15:40.730 --> 15:42.148
Appreciate the offer, Chief,

15:42.232 --> 15:44.255
but prison has changed me.

15:44.339 --> 15:48.152
Now I'm thinking I should just
give up, serve out my term,

15:48.236 --> 15:51.690
then sit in the warm sun
outside the butcher shop.

15:51.774 --> 15:53.110
Isn't that what you always did?

15:53.194 --> 15:55.309
Yeah, but every few hours,

15:55.393 --> 15:57.903
someone would whisper
something into my ear,

15:57.987 --> 16:01.148
then I had to decide
whether to nod or shrug.

16:01.232 --> 16:04.705
It was very stressful. The agita.

16:04.789 --> 16:07.514
Uh, I thought you wanted to
get the guy who put you here.

16:07.598 --> 16:08.910
I do.

16:08.994 --> 16:11.810
Well, we will, if you will wear a wire.

16:11.894 --> 16:15.697
I'm sorry, but on principle,
that is something I cannot do.

16:15.781 --> 16:20.126
Let me repeat: something I cannot do.

16:21.278 --> 16:23.671
♪ ♪

16:42.132 --> 16:43.191
(tires screech)

16:44.685 --> 16:47.309
Now, remember the phrase
to call for help.

16:47.393 --> 16:49.222
- What phrase?
- "Remember the phrase."

16:49.306 --> 16:51.268
I will. What phrase is it?

16:51.352 --> 16:53.277
"Remember the phrase."

16:53.361 --> 16:56.539
I would if you would tell me what it is.

16:56.623 --> 16:58.775
The phrase is "remember the phrase."

16:58.859 --> 17:01.629
That is the dumbest
thing I've ever heard.

17:01.713 --> 17:03.546
Just remember, your life depends on us.

17:03.630 --> 17:05.486
Oh, and please, no profanity.

17:05.569 --> 17:07.031
I play these for the missus

17:07.116 --> 17:09.126
when we're, uh, we're
getting in the mood.

17:09.210 --> 17:10.218
(laughs)

17:11.346 --> 17:13.130
(groans)

17:13.214 --> 17:16.724
A toast to Fat Tony, a man
like a Botticelli nude:

17:16.809 --> 17:19.060
fat, old and easy to frame, huh?

17:19.145 --> 17:20.921
(laughter)

17:21.005 --> 17:22.897
Hello, fellas.

17:22.982 --> 17:24.808
Fat Tony. I was just saying
how much we missed you.

17:24.892 --> 17:26.378
Huh? Huh, guys?

17:26.463 --> 17:28.570
- Oh, yeah, sure. Yeah, we said that.
- (nervous murmuring)

17:28.655 --> 17:30.406
Quiet! I don't want to hear anybody

17:30.490 --> 17:32.649
but Frankie the Squealer.

17:32.733 --> 17:35.201
W-W-What do, w-what do you
want to hear from me?

17:39.407 --> 17:41.624
The name of the man who
framed you? I would never.

17:41.708 --> 17:43.464
I didn't say Johnny Tightlips.

17:43.548 --> 17:45.092
I would never say Johnny Tightlips.

17:45.176 --> 17:47.423
Ladies and gentlemen, our
new boss, Johnny Tightlips.

17:47.507 --> 17:50.426
So, it was you, Johnny.

17:50.510 --> 17:53.035
- What? Hey! Whoa!
- You!

17:53.119 --> 17:56.052
After all your
passive-aggressive replies

17:56.136 --> 17:59.205
and bitter looks, I
never would've guessed.

17:59.289 --> 18:02.368
You mistook my taciturn
nature for fealty.

18:02.452 --> 18:04.631
But it was simply that I
didn't feel comfortable

18:04.715 --> 18:06.275
in social situations.

18:06.359 --> 18:07.968
Then I saw this commercial

18:08.052 --> 18:11.630
where a sad cloud goes
on a date with the sun.

18:11.714 --> 18:14.225
So I talked to my doctor about Paxil,

18:14.309 --> 18:17.453
and it gave me the
confidence to betray you.

18:17.537 --> 18:20.105
(agreeable chatter)

18:20.189 --> 18:24.017
This is my crew now. Ain't
that right, Jimmy Kissass?

18:24.101 --> 18:25.819
You was always my favorite.

18:25.903 --> 18:28.001
What about you, Sonny Go-along?

18:28.085 --> 18:29.955
I'm good if everyone else is.

18:30.039 --> 18:32.013
- Willie Whatever?
- Whatever.

18:32.097 --> 18:34.523
And you, Joey Can't-Read-the-Room?

18:34.607 --> 18:37.185
You're nuts! Ain't none of
us gonna go along with this!

18:37.269 --> 18:39.557
Yeah, see, that's... You
didn't... that's not...

18:42.136 --> 18:43.352
(bottle shatters)

18:47.883 --> 18:49.342
("Don't Stop Believin'"
by Journey playing)

18:49.426 --> 18:51.728
♪ <i>Just a small town girl...</i> ♪

18:51.812 --> 18:53.874
I'm surprised Maggie isn't here.

18:53.958 --> 18:56.400
♪ <i>Lonely world</i> ♪

18:56.484 --> 18:58.518
♪ <i>She took the midnight train</i> ♪

18:58.602 --> 19:01.572
♪ <i>Going anywhere...</i> ♪

19:01.656 --> 19:04.505
Mmm, this pasta's delicious.

19:04.589 --> 19:06.217
I'm gonna find out what the sauce is.

19:06.301 --> 19:08.212
Remember the phrase.

19:08.296 --> 19:10.080
<i>WIGGUM (over radio):
Remember what phrase?</i>

19:10.164 --> 19:12.155
<i>- Oh, right.</i>
- (siren wailing)

19:15.244 --> 19:17.428
Ooh, sauce.

19:20.841 --> 19:22.266
Oh! I'm hit!

19:24.011 --> 19:26.926
Right in the heart... of your ass.

19:27.010 --> 19:29.766
Someone's got to suck out the bullet.

19:29.850 --> 19:32.886
Wiggum, damn it, this is
what you were born to do.

19:32.970 --> 19:34.605
(sucking)

19:34.689 --> 19:36.489
- ♪<i> Don't stop...</i> ♪
- (music stops abruptly)

19:39.031 --> 19:40.318
There he is.

19:40.402 --> 19:42.854
We thought we were gonna lose
you for a minute there, champ.

19:42.938 --> 19:44.522
(laughs)

19:44.606 --> 19:46.191
You have the chief here to thank.

19:46.275 --> 19:48.417
His quick suction may
have saved your life.

19:49.611 --> 19:50.794
(hoarse): Thank you.

19:53.782 --> 19:57.672
Well, Wiggum, I have to say,
when I first met you,

19:57.756 --> 19:59.555
I thought you were totally incompetent.

19:59.639 --> 20:01.632
(chuckles)

20:01.716 --> 20:03.073
And?

20:04.626 --> 20:06.479
- And?
- (tires screech)

20:06.563 --> 20:09.714
And?! A-And?! And?!

20:09.798 --> 20:11.825
I believe in you, Chief.

20:11.909 --> 20:14.275
And, yeah, that-that's enough.

20:17.094 --> 20:19.933
The three of us, we are
not that different.

20:20.017 --> 20:21.730
Whoa! Hey, whoa!

20:21.814 --> 20:23.395
What's this guy talking about?

20:23.479 --> 20:25.563
We are <i> cicciobomba,</i>

20:25.647 --> 20:29.234
who like to sit in the sun
and enjoy a nice prosciutto.

20:29.318 --> 20:31.780
<i>Cicciobomba,</i> prosciutto.

20:31.864 --> 20:34.114
You guys make garbage sound good.

20:34.198 --> 20:37.450
We call garbage <i> spazzatura.</i>

20:37.944 --> 20:41.454
Mmm... garbage.

20:41.538 --> 20:43.756
- (laughter)
- Garbage.

